column5:
Fixed $ref handling in schema editing

Fix to be able to handle $ref properties while editing  json schema.

Example:
{
"id": "http://some.site.somewhere/entry-schema#",
"$schema": "http://json-schema.org/draft-04/schema#",
"description": "schema for an $ref entry",
"type": "object",
"properties": {
"$ref": {
"type": "string"
}
}
}

Update lz-string script url

@pieroxy reorganized files in lz-string repository:
https://github.com/pieroxy/lz-string/commit/9f65f29

Now all buttons have a css-class specifying its function

It is now possible to hide edit- and collapse-buttons like this:

    <style>

        .json-editor-btn-edit
        {
            display: none;
        }

        .json-editor-btn-collapse
        {
            display: none;
        }
    </style>

Add api methods for listening for ready/change events.

```js
// Listen for an event
editor.on('change', function() {});

// Stop listening for an event
editor.off('change', my_function);

// Remove all listeners for an event
editor.off('change');

// Remove all listeners for all events
editor.off();
```

The jQuery wrapper emits DOM events like before, so there is no change there.
